This paper focuses on multi-robot motion planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of sampling-based planners, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for motion planning. The paper also presents a new method for convergence to optimal paths, which is related to control theory (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the applicability of the method to high-dimensional problems, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
